      • ciCheck

        boolean ciCheck​(int lotvalue)
        This function is used to check in the parkinglots array for the particular slot(A or B or C or D or E) that user have asked for, if there is space for the vehicle to get parked
        Parameters:
        lotvalue -
        Returns:
        - boolean true if the space is available in parking lot, boolean false if there is no space available in parking lot

      • allocate

        java.lang.String allocate​(int lotvalue,
                          java.lang.String vnumber,
                          java.lang.String vtype,
                          java.lang.String entrytime,
                          char lotname)
                   throws java.text.ParseException
        This function is used to allocate the slot for the vehicle after the ciCheck method add the value of the vehicle number and entry time to the pricecache add the value of the vehicle number and lotname to the freearraypricecache add the value of the vehicle type and entry time to the vehicletypecache
        Parameters:
        lotvalue - - value of the parking lot (A,B,C,D,E) in an integer format
        vnumber - - vehicle number of the vehicle to be parked
        vtype - - type of the vehicle
        entrytime - - entry time of the vehicle during check-in
        lotname - - value of the parking lot (A,B,C,D,E)
        Returns:
        the success message if the vehicle checked-in
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException
